---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ProjectDeadlineCalculator from '../components/ProjectDeadlineCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Project Deadline Calculator — Working Days Until Deadline | Clockr"
	description="Calculate working days until your project deadline or find the finish date after a set number of working days. Free deadline calculator with weekend and public holiday options."
	category="work"
>
	<div class="pdc-page">
		<div class="pdc-header">
			<div class="pdc-eyebrow">
				<span class="pdc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				Work & Business
			</div>
			<h1 class="pdc-title">
				<span class="pdc-gradient">Project Deadline Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="pdc-subtitle">Work out exactly how long you have until your deadline</p>
		</div>

		<ProjectDeadlineCalculator client:load />

		<section class="pdc-how">
			<h2 class="pdc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="pdc-how-card">
				<p>
					Project deadlines in the real world rarely line up with calendar days.
					Most teams work Monday to Friday, so a &ldquo;10-day&rdquo; sprint might
					span two full weeks on the calendar once weekends are accounted for.
					Public holidays add another layer — a deadline set in working days can
					slip by several calendar days if bank holidays fall in between. For
					accurate project planning, working days matter more than raw calendar
					days because they reflect when work actually gets done.
				</p>
				<p>
					Clockr offers two modes. &ldquo;Time until deadline&rdquo; counts down
					from today (or your project start date) to a fixed deadline, showing
					calendar days, working days, and a weeks-and-days breakdown. A progress
					bar appears when your start date is today or in the past, visualising
					time elapsed versus time remaining. &ldquo;Calculate finish date&rdquo;
					works in the opposite direction — enter a start date and a number of
					working days, and the tool calculates when the project should be
					complete.
				</p>
				<p>
					You can choose to include or exclude weekends, and optionally subtract
					public holidays using standard UK or US holiday schedules as a guide.
					Public holiday dates vary by region, employer, and year — some
					jurisdictions observe substitute days when a holiday falls on a weekend,
					and not every organisation closes on the same dates. Treat the holiday
					option as a planning estimate and adjust manually for your local
					calendar where precision matters.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="pdc-faq">
			<h2 class="pdc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="pdc-faq-list">
				<details class="pdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdc-faq-question"
						>How do I calculate working days until a deadline?</summary
					>
					<div class="pdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Select &ldquo;Time until deadline&rdquo;, enter your project start
							date and deadline date, and leave &ldquo;Exclude weekends&rdquo;
							selected. The calculator shows how many working days remain from
							today to your deadline. Optionally check &ldquo;Exclude public
							holidays&rdquo; and choose UK or US to subtract bank holidays that
							fall within the range.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="pdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdc-faq-question">What counts as a working day?</summary>
					<div class="pdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							By default, a working day is any weekday — Monday through Friday.
							Saturday and Sunday are excluded unless you switch to &ldquo;Include
							weekends&rdquo;. When public holiday exclusion is enabled, recognised
							bank holidays for your selected country are also removed from the
							working day count, even when they fall on a weekday.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="pdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdc-faq-question"
						>How do I find out what date is 30 working days from today?</summary
					>
					<div class="pdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Switch to &ldquo;Calculate finish date&rdquo;, set the start date to
							today, enter 30 in the working days field, and keep weekends
							excluded. The result shows the calendar date that is exactly 30
							weekdays later, skipping any Saturdays and Sundays along the way.
							Enable public holiday exclusion if you want bank holidays subtracted
							too.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="pdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdc-faq-question"
						>Does this calculator exclude public holidays?</summary
					>
					<div class="pdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Only when you check &ldquo;Exclude public holidays&rdquo;. By default
							the tool counts weekdays only and does not subtract bank holidays.
							When enabled, it uses standard UK bank holidays or US federal
							holidays as a guide — including movable dates like Good Friday and
							Thanksgiving. Regional variations and employer-specific closures are
							not covered automatically.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="pdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdc-faq-question"
						>How many working days are in a month?</summary
					>
					<div class="pdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Most months contain between 20 and 23 weekdays, depending on how
							weekends fall. A 31-day month with five full weekends can have as
							few as 20 working days, while a month starting on a Friday can have
							23. Public holidays reduce the count further. Use the Business Days
							Calculator for a detailed month-by-month breakdown of any year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="pdc-faq-item">
					<summary class="pdc-faq-question"
						>Can I use this for project management planning?</summary
					>
					<div class="pdc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. The countdown mode helps you see how much runway remains on a
							fixed deadline, while the finish-date mode answers &ldquo;when will
							we be done if we have X working days of effort?&rdquo; — useful for
							sprint planning, contract milestones, and delivery estimates. Pair
							it with the Work Hours Calculator to convert working days into
							actual labour hours for your team.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="pdc-related">
			<h3 class="pdc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="pdc-related-grid">
				<a href="/business-days" class="pdc-related-card"
					><span class="pdc-related-name">Business Days Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/work-hours-calculator" class="pdc-related-card"
					><span class="pdc-related-name">Work Hours Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/overtime-calculator" class="pdc-related-card"
					><span class="pdc-related-name">Overtime Calculator</span></a
				>
				<a href="/countdown-timer" class="pdc-related-card"
					><span class="pdc-related-name">Countdown Timer</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.pdc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.pdc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.pdc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.pdc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdc-gradient {
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.pdc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.pdc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.pdc-tabs {
		display: flex;
		gap: 8px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.2);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 6px;
	}

	.pdc-tab {
		flex: 1;
		background: transparent;
		border: none;
		border-radius: 10px;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			background 0.2s ease,
			color 0.2s ease;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	.pdc-tab:hover {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
	}

	.pdc-tab--active {
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		color: #fff;
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.1);
	}

	.pdc-form-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.2);
		border-radius: 20px;
		padding: 32px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.06);
	}

	:global(.rcc-inputs) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 18px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input-wrap) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 10px;
		align-items: stretch;
	}

	:global(.rcc-label) {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		letter-spacing: 0.5px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input) {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 16px 24px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 24px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #ffffff;
		text-align: center;
		outline: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
		width: 100%;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(.rcc-input:focus) {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.8);
		box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
	}

	.pdc-options {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 20px;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.12);
		padding-top: 24px;
	}

	.pdc-toggle-group {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 10px;
	}

	.pdc-toggle-btn {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.3);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 14px 12px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease,
			color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.pdc-toggle-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.6);
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.08);
	}

	.pdc-toggle-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-to-rgb), 0.7);
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.12);
		color: #fff;
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.1);
	}

	.pdc-holiday-row {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 16px;
	}

	.pdc-checkbox {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 10px;
		cursor: pointer;
		user-select: none;
	}

	.pdc-checkbox input {
		position: absolute;
		opacity: 0;
		width: 0;
		height: 0;
	}

	.pdc-checkbox-box {
		width: 20px;
		height: 20px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.4);
		border-radius: 6px;
		background: #0c0c0c;
		flex-shrink: 0;
		position: relative;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.pdc-checkbox input:checked + .pdc-checkbox-box {
		background: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.2);
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-to-rgb), 0.7);
	}

	.pdc-checkbox input:checked + .pdc-checkbox-box::after {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		left: 6px;
		top: 2px;
		width: 5px;
		height: 10px;
		border: solid #fff;
		border-width: 0 2px 2px 0;
		transform: rotate(45deg);
	}

	.pdc-checkbox-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
	}

	.pdc-select {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.3);
		border-radius: 10px;
		padding: 10px 14px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: #fff;
		outline: none;
		cursor: pointer;
		color-scheme: dark;
	}

	.pdc-select:focus {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.8);
	}

	.pdc-results {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 20px;
	}

	.pdc-stats-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.pdc-stat-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 20px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.pdc-stat-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin-bottom: 8px;
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
		line-height: 1.4;
	}

	.pdc-stat-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 36px;
		font-weight: 800;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		line-height: 1.1;
		margin-bottom: 6px;
	}

	.pdc-stat-sub {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
	}

	.pdc-holiday-note {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.pdc-progress {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 20px;
	}

	.pdc-progress-top {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	.pdc-progress-track {
		height: 10px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 999px;
		overflow: hidden;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	.pdc-progress-fill {
		height: 100%;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		border-radius: 999px;
		transition: width 0.3s ease;
	}

	.pdc-progress-labels {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
	}

	.pdc-finish-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.25);
		border-radius: 16px;
		padding: 32px 24px;
		text-align: center;
		box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.08);
	}

	.pdc-finish-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		margin-bottom: 12px;
		letter-spacing: 0.3px;
	}

	.pdc-finish-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 32px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		line-height: 1.2;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 12px;
	}

	.pdc-finish-sub {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.pdc-error {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 120, 120, 0.85);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 16px;
		background: rgba(255, 80, 80, 0.06);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 80, 80, 0.15);
		border-radius: 12px;
	}

	.pdc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.pdc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.pdc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.pdc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.pdc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.pdc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.pdc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.pdc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.pdc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.pdc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.pdc-faq-item[open] .pdc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.pdc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.pdc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.pdc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.pdc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.pdc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.pdc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.pdc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(var(--cat-from-rgb), 0.4);
	}

	.pdc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: var(--cat-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.pdc-title {
			font-size: 40px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.pdc-tab {
			font-size: 12px;
			padding: 12px 10px;
		}

		.pdc-stats-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.pdc-stat-num {
			font-size: 28px;
		}

		.pdc-finish-date {
			font-size: 24px;
		}

		.pdc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
